org.jcvi.jillion.sam.attribute

Interface SamAttributeValidator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NoDuplicateAttributeValidator, ReservedAttributeValidator
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface SamAttributeValidator
    Validates SamAttributes using different criteria.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • validate

        void validate(SamHeader header,
              SamAttributed source,
              SamAttribute attribute)
       throws InvalidAttributeException
        Validates that the given SamAttribute is valid and throws an InvalidAttributeException if the validation fails.
        Parameters:
        header - the header for this SamAttribute which may define this attribute.
        source - where this attribute came from; usually a SamRecord; will never be null.
        attribute - the SamAttribute to validate; will never be null.
        Throws:
        InvalidAttributeException - if the validation fails.
        NullPointerException - if any parameter is null.

      • thenValidating

        default SamAttributeValidator thenValidating(SamAttributeValidator other)
        Creates a new SamAttributeValidator that is a two validators chained together. "this" validator is called, first and if it "passes" an attribute, then the other validator in the chain gets called.

        The attribute only passes the chained validator if all the validators in the chain also pass the attribute. If any validator throws an exception, then that exception is thrown by the chain and no other validators in the chain are called.

        Parameters:
        other - the other SamAttributeValidator to call next in the chain; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new SamAttributeValidator that chains "this" validator and the other validator.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if other is null.
        Since:
        5.0
